element_texts.text:
April 1918
You have been staying in the center of my mind for the last tow or three days and I hope it is not because your illness has taken a bad turn. Now that the spring days have come you must get well and go out of doors.
I have, for the first time been reading some of the tales of Pushkin. In this connection I am wondering why you try at all to fit yourself to be a [unclear] of writing. Something -- perhaps your worlds about May Sinclair's book
